File: Since September, over 12,000 depositors with balances amounting to nearly R260-million had activated their accounts but more than 5,500 have not yet done so. eNCA JOHANNESBURG - Qualifying VBS retail customers who have not yet claimed their deposits at Nedbank have until 8 July next year to do so. Since September, over 12,000 depositors with balances amounting to nearly R260-million had activated their accounts but more than 5,500 have not yet done so. WATCH: VBS customers get their cash VBS bank was placed under curatorship by Finance Minister in March 2018. In July of the same year, the South African Reserve Bank announced that qualifying retail depositors could have access to their deposits at any Nedbank branch. A total of 171 individuals claimed, amounting to over R41-million.